现在，我们来看看流利度构建器。

190
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:16,040
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

191
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:22,480
So with Fluency Builder, we take some very simple phrases and show you how you can be
通过流利度构建器，我们选取一些非常简单的短语，并向你展示如何能

192
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:25,440
more fluent or how you can...
更流利，或者如何能……

193
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,440
Sound more native.
听起来更地道。

194
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,440
Yeah.
是的。

195
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,440
Great.
太好了。

196
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:32,440
In the beginning of the dialogue, Anna said, Nick, how's it going?
在对话开头，安娜说：“尼克，最近怎么样？”

197
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,840
Yeah, this is a great phrase.
是的，这是一个很棒的短语。

198
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,140
It sounds really, really natural.
听起来非常非常自然。

199
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:39,920
You know, sometimes I hear students say, how are you?
你知道，有时我听到学生说“你好吗？”

200
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:41,920
Or, how are you doing?
或者“你怎么样？”

201
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:46,840
Those are two great phrases, but this one sounds really, really natural.
这两个短语都很棒，但这个听起来非常非常自然。

202
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,760
It just sounds more casual.
它听起来更随意。

203
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:53,840
Yeah, let's listen again to that phrase from the dialogue.
是的，我们再听一遍对话中的那个短语。

204
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:56,760
How's it going?
最近怎么样？

205
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,360
How's it going?
最近怎么样？

206
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,640
Great.
很好。

207
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:04,120
So next time that you find a friend on the street, you can just say, hey, how's it going?
所以下次你在街上遇到朋友时，可以直接说，嘿，最近怎么样？

208
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,120
Yeah.
是的。

209
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,400
So Marco, have you ever forgotten someone's name?
那么马可，你有没有忘记过别人的名字？

210
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,440
Yeah, it's happened to me a couple of times.
有，我遇到过几次。

211
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:15,960
And actually, the most embarrassing situation was that I forgot a family member's name.
实际上，最尴尬的一次是我忘记了一个家人的名字。

212
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:17,720
No, a family member's name.
不会吧，家人的名字。

213
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:23,160
We had like a family reunion and there were a lot of aunts and uncles and cousins that
我们当时有个家庭聚会，有很多叔叔、阿姨和堂兄弟姐妹，

214
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,560
I hadn't seen in a while.
我很久没见他们了。

215
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:27,240
And I just forgot one of my uncle's names.
然后我就忘记了我一个叔叔的名字。

216
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,240
And I was...
我当时……

217
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,240
Uh-oh, that's pretty embarrassing.
哎呀，那太尴尬了。

218
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,240
Yeah.
是啊。

219
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,240
So what did you do?
那你怎么办了？

220
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,440
Well, I had to ask one of my other cousins.
嗯，我不得不问我的一个堂兄弟。

221
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,440
I'm like, hey, who is that guy?
我说，嘿，那个人是谁？

222
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,000
He's like, oh, that's Uncle John.
他说，哦，那是约翰叔叔。

223
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,440
I'm like, oh man, I totally forgot.
我说，哦天哪，我完全忘了。

224
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,440
Yeah.
是啊。

225
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:41,960
So it was really embarrassing because I didn't know what to call him.
所以真的很尴尬，因为我不知道该怎么称呼他。

226
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:45,080
So I just called him Uncle because I didn't know his name.
所以我只好叫他叔叔，因为我不知道他的名字。

227
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,080
Hi, Uncle.
嗨，叔叔。

228
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,080
Yeah.
是啊。

229
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,080
Oh, yeah.
哦，对。

230
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:53,680
So when that happens to me, when I'm in a business setting, sometimes what I do is I
所以当我遇到这种情况时，如果是在商务场合，我有时会

231
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,480
ask for someone's card.
问别人要名片。

232
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,520
Yeah, that's the good technique.
嗯，这是个好办法。

233
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,520
Yeah.
是的。

234
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:02,680
Or sometimes I might ask them to write down their email because usually their full name
或者有时我会让他们写下邮箱，因为通常他们的全名

235
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:04,160
is spelled in their email address.
会拼写在邮箱地址里。

236
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:06,760
So that's my trick when I've forgotten someone's name.
这就是我忘记别人名字时的小窍门。

237
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,760
That's a good trick.
好主意。

238
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:11,480
And I guess a lot of our listeners can take your advice on that.
我想很多听众可以采纳你的建议。

239
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,480
Okay.
好的。

240
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:18,040
So I think it's time for us to listen to our dialogue one more time, this time at natural
所以我想是时候再听一遍我们的对话了，这次是正常语速。

241
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:21,040
speed.
速度。

242
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:27,960
Nick, how's it going?
尼克，最近怎么样？

243
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,960
Oh, hey.
哦，嘿。

244
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:32,040
What are you doing in this neighborhood?
你在这个街区做什么？

245
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,280
Do you live around here?
你住在这附近吗？

246
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:36,280
Actually, my office is right around the corner.
其实，我的办公室就在拐角处。

247
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:38,520
It was great to meet you last week at the conference.
上周在会议上见到你真是太好了。

248
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,960
I really enjoyed our conversation about foreign investment.
我真的很喜欢我们关于外国投资的讨论。

249
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:41,960
Yeah, yeah.
是啊，是啊。

250
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:44,560
It was really interesting.
真的很有趣。

251
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:47,360
You know, I'm in a bit of a hurry, but here's my card.
你知道，我有点赶时间，但这是我的名片。

252
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:50,160
We should definitely meet up again and continue our discussion.
我们一定要再见面，继续我们的讨论。

253
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:51,160
Sure.
当然。

254
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:53,680
You still have my contact details, right?
你还有我的联系方式，对吧？

255
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:54,920
You know what?
你知道吗？

256
00:10:54,920 --> 00:10:58,400
This is really embarrassing, but your name has just slipped my mind.
这真的很尴尬，但我一时想不起你的名字了。

257
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,960
Can you remind me?
你能提醒我一下吗？

258
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:00,960
Sure.
当然。

259
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,160
My name is Anna Farris.
我叫安娜·法里斯。

260
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,160
Don't worry about it.
别担心。

261
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,720
You say this to me all the time.
你总是这样对我说。

262
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:08,040
I'm terrible with names too.
我也不擅长记名字。

263
